origReviewText: Over the years I have probably owned 30 or 40 pairs of Arcopedico mules.  The stretch fabric on top makes these shoes comfortable and the soles give great support.  I like the fact that they are washable and have a leather foot bed.  I do wish this company would offer replacement insoles because these wear out before the shoe does.  Inquiries to the company in this regard have brought no response.
Love these shoes. I have very painful feet .  toes , bunions too. These shoes have been a God send to me.

Had these some years ago. Lately , I am suffering from Edema and particularly in the instep. I was having trouble finding any shoe that fit. Bought these again and with the stretch in the instep - I can wear shoes again and not slippers. I am ordering them in several colors.
Great boots, look fantastic, really comfortable and perfect fit. Will now buy some more!
They have a very foul oder .
Handsome boots, and very comfortable.
Too tight for sandals, especially in toe.
The best Sandles made

Let me start by saying I have narrow feet - a 10.5 A or 11.0 A depending on the shoe. These are 10.5 M.. These Keen sandals are petty darn good. I never had sandals until I ordered a pair of Birkenstock Arizona 'Birko-Flor', which I hated; open toe and a ridge between your toe & foot - they really hurt my feet!. These Keen (closed toe) can be worn all-day in comfort - I really like my Keen Newport.
I love Keens and this pair did not disappoint.  I haven't the Bison variety before and so far I am very pleased with the feel of the shoe.
This is not the same product I bought in stores

I am not one to wear sandals or flip flops. I found these keens about two years ago in a locally owned shoe store and decided to give them a try.  Other than smelling some once worn they are a great summer shoe/sandal.  Toes stay protected.  Very stable whether walking, biking, boating, jet skiing you name it.  I really like the microfiber foot sole.  I tried another pair of the brighter colors  but they have a plastic footbed so I returned them and ordered these.  Perfect.  I was going back and forth on the size and bought the larger size.  Fits very comfortable.
Love these? Nuff said.
I purchased the Keen sandals after buying a few other cheaper brands. No comparison with comfort. They seem well constructed but time will tell on that.
My dad loves them!
What I expected . . Maybe should have tried for a wide but I like them a lot.
I love Keen Newport sandles.

After trying several brands of similar looking shoes at local stores, that didn't even last for a season, it was suggested that I try Keene.  I am so glad that I did.  They fit perfectly and comfortably right from the beginning.  I can't tell how they will wear yet, but at this time I am completely satisfied.
So far these sandals are very comfortable and would recommend them for anyone
The first pair lasted almost 10 years of near-daily wear.  The new ones run a bit narrower than the originals but are still comfy.  I look forward to another decade of comfort.

first pair lasted many years of daily wear and soles finally started separating, so this is my second pair. I like the softer footbed of the regular Newports, but you do have to clean them (footbed) to keep them nice and not stinky and slick, is my recommendation.
this is my 2nd pair of Keen sandals, the fit, comfort & support are exactly what I expected, great summer-time wear, happy consumer here.
Great shoes for running around!
Comfortable for day to day walking. Have not yet used them at the beach.. The elastic draw string "lace" makes for easy comfort adjustment. Pressure points can easily be taken care of.. worth the $$
Have had these before. They never wear out!
My third pair of these; wear them constantly, all year through. Have a pair of boat shoes as well and wear them when weather is too nasty for these.
Fits well, comfortable and durable.

This issue of shoes is slightly smaller than the old pair I had of the exact same style.  Still should work.  I had an old 43 that was perfect for my 10-10 1/2 foot, but these are a little tight.  The 44 is too big, though.
My third pair  Great Great Great
Great shoe. Last pair lasted ten years. Hoping to get ten years out of this one.
Second pair of Newports. Got seven yrs and many miles on the first pair. Perfect blend of comfort protection and durability.
very well made, and comfortable to wear.
Really love keen shoes, they fit great and are instantly comfortable.
The fit, look, comfort are excellent. The cloth straps used to put on the sandal snap off easily.. Even then, no regrets for the comfort and style.
I bought these for my husband to wear at the cabin and he loves them.  He is in and out of the water so they work perfect!  They are also just a good casual to wear with his shorts and jeans.
great sandals, hope they last as long as my previous pair.
No complaints, hold up great hiking on trails.
Excellent shoes. Comfortable and protects yer toes. Handy pull cord to tighten and a quick release mechanism when you want to take them off.

i find it comfortable and easy to walk in.. I normally wear orthotic insolds.  i've walked quite a few miles now, no sore spots, and just comfortable.. they are a bit heavy, but for comfort, I'm all in.

LOVE THEM!  They fit well and they're very comfortable.  I usually wear a 12 and these 12s are spot-on.  Wish they were a tad wider (I usually wear a wide), but they'll do as is.  I will put a lot of miles on these.  I just learned about Keens this year.  The two pair I've purchased are fantastic!
I join the very long line of approvers of these sandals. I think they are great. Exceedingly comfortable, and I can walk 5 miles in them no worries at all.
2nd pair after 10 years on the first. Fantastic fit and performance!
Very comfortable!  Will be buying more !
Have had several pairs of this Keen style; glad to find them at Amazon!  I have problem feet and these shoes solve that problem without having to use orthotics!

I own several pair of Keen Newport 2 sandals. They fit my long, narrow feet better than any sandal I have ever owned. The rubber toe guard does not compress your toes and there have been a few times they have protected my toes while walking on uneven ground/rocks. The leather pair are somewhat less weather resistant and take time to dry-out after exposure to water. Overall, I am very pleased with Keen's construction and will buy other shoes and boots from their company because of my positive experience with their sandals.

Great, sturdy and comfortable shoe.  Bought it for my husband's birthday and he prefers it over a similar style by a different brand.  He says the cushion is better and the shoe is all round more comfortable.  Seems to be a better quality.  so we didn't mind spending a little more than was what was offered at local sports academy for less.
These are great! Sturdy and comfortable
I've had another pair of Keen's that are nylon.  They are a few years old and the stitching is coming apart.  Hoping the leather version works better.
I wear an 8 1/2 shoe and find I always buy my keens 1/2 size larger.  They are perfect and last for years and years.

The KEEN's Men's Newport Sandals are the perfect fusion of sandals, sneakers and outdoor shoes.  It is no wonder that Steve Jobs liked wearing them along with his Birkenstocks. My first pair of KEEN Men's Newport Sandals lasted almost 8 years and a racked up a lot of mileage on them.  From hiking trips in Japan, walking on the beaches in Shimoda, Miura Kaigan and Hawaii to city walks in LA, Tokyo and NYC, the sandals have never disappointed me.  Perfect to wear with or without socks and sole has good arch support making each step very comfortable.  The covered rubber toe gives good protection especially when you're on the mountain trails and has a more stylish look.  These shoes will certainly last a long time and will be a your all-time favorite.
These sandals are so well made and come in a meriad of colors.  The fit is so comfortable that I wore them all day long the first day I got them and I ended up getting a pair for the whole family.
Built for a very slim men's size.
The shoes fit perfectly, just as anticipated.
One shoe is a little smaller than the other
Very sturdy comfort and quality sandal

My husband loves these sandals he wears them year round. They are very popular, because it is difficult to find in his size unless you like all one color. Amazon does a great job of giving you variety as well as great shipping. The shoe is well made and worth the money.
These sandals last a long time, they hose right off and clean up nicely.

I have wide feet that swell up after waking around all day so sometimes these shoes can be a little too snug even though I've loosened the straps up as much as possible.  **the guy at the store helped my fix the straps to fit my feet so I know they're right** besides my personal issue cuz of my wide feet these are the best most comfortable sandal I've ever purchased. These are worth the money 100% I hiked around Europe in these, gone bike riding, helped friends move, ect. in these and they never let me down.
Well made and cute but too much arch for my flat feet. Otherwise the straps adjusted well and seemed to stay put as I tried them out around the house on my thin feet.

The shoes fit well,are true to size, and very comfortable. They were also worth what I paid for them.  I'm  happy to have found them, because I've had a hard time  finding the perfect shoe and/or sandals I want for this Summer. :)
I love them! They are just as expected.

My right foot is a little larger than the left, so I was totally flabbergasted when I first tried them on and the left foot was really tight and the right foot was comfortable.  Needless to say, they went BACK.

soo.  bought these for my sister for her birthday back in may bc I remember these were the EXACT ones she wore back in the 80s and 90s. then they went MIA, no idea why, they were the shiznit. but style and times have changed, so if you want these, you have to pay the price. I got the size my sister has always worn, which is an 8 1/2, but they are super tight on her. they do stretch, so it will take some time. but she has only put them on maybe twice bc theyre so tight, so I feel like I wasted my money. the product is great, I just should've gotten a size 9 and now its too late to switch. ugh!  . packaged well and brand spankin new. thanks!.
product I as described and shoes are comfortable and attractive.  A good value.

For a gardener these are the best choice.  I had a pair that lasted for years and years.  I didn't think I would find another pair like them as they quit offering them in my community.  I bought another brand with some kind of bonded lining that was always getting wet, dirty or muddy.  I hated that.  The Slogger is so easy to clean out, just a hosing will do.  I love it that you can wear them and get them full of water.  Just dump it out and your good to go.  The only reason mine wore out finally was the tread wore out after miles and miles of use.  They were so slick that when I went down a steep hill in my yard I would fall down or I would probably still be wearing them.  My granddaughter fell heir to them as she is more sure footed.  The material is very sturdy and durable.  They exceed in comfort.  Presently I'm using a third pair of some unknown brand that have worn callouses on several places on my foot and are beginning to tear at the edges after just one season of use!  Can't wait to get the replacement Slogger.
Good product and service
Great price, fit as expected. I have to have white shoes for nursing school and these fit the bill.

This is my all time favorite shoes to wear!!! I work for the county and I deal a lot of walking back and forward to assist clients. It's a fast pace environment and these shoes helped me soo much. They feel like tennis shoes and they still looks soo professional. I've had my first pair for an year, in ready to buy my second pair. I bought a pair for my sister and my mom. I recomend these shoes for Christmas gift too. I love them.

these are the only nursing shoes I have ever worn. they are comfortable, and my feet never hurt after 12 hour shifts. it is hard for me to find comfortable shoes, but these are the best. No need to try other shoes. these are not as expensive as some of the bigger name brands and they are more comfortable.
Returned this size & ordered 1 star l size larger still to tight. ALL of my other sites are 10W.
I have been wearing this shoe for years. Very comfortable :-)
Really like these shoes, my feet feel great. Will recommend these to my friends.
great product delivered on time

A decent price for this boot.  DO order a size that is slightly smaller than shoe size.  Mine were about a half size to big.  No return label was sent with this product, so I'm guessing you have to pay for a different size boot.  Oh well, I'll just wear an extra pair of ankle socks with my regular socks.
THIS PAIR OF BOOTS ARE A CLONE FOR A PAIR I`VE BEEN WEARING FOR THE LAST 6 YEARS. I LIKE THEM.
Boots are a perfect fit had them delivered in two days with it awesome.  Very happy with this purchase!
Very comfortable.  i would recommend this shoes to anyone that needs comfort.
Rugged and sturdy shoe, made to take a cold winter's walk.

Nice shoes, but you won't be able to add an insole in these it'll be too tight.  The toe box vertical height is perfect if you're just wearing socks, but if you add an insole you're toes will rub against the top of the shoes.
Great everything I wanted in a shoe
These are now the hippest shoes in my cupboard next to my cowboy boots, very cumfy
Very comfortable and well made.  Expect a break-in period of perhaps two weeks, but a really nice fit afterward.
Great shoes. Thanks so much!!!.-

Although shoes fit as expected, found these were not. as forgiving as other Clark's I own when being on my. feet for hours at a time. They have a harder foot bed and. crepe sole seemed noticeably denser than my other Clark's.
Once you have worn one pair you will want all the colot.
Product runs a size large, but is of excellent quality.  Very stylish.  Goes well with jeans or casual dress, and the seller was very easy to deal with.  Highly recommend.

I love these, extremely comfortable. Though how high they are gets the jokes from my friends and is a bit weird at first. I made the mistake of going only a half size smaller and then wearing them out. Now  stuck with shoes that are too big.
I love it, it's the real deal.  It's comfy, I will buy again.
It fits as expected to for I know it might stretch buy it for back to school and needed something to last for the year or more
Not the same shoes as described. They sent me another model.
It was hard to clean it when it got dirty.  I couldn't get the colour to dye it.
Very comfortable. Quite saucy.
This was bought for a friend.  He has extra wide feet. He wears them daily.
My wife loves these shoes. Comfy,  sleek,  and priced right
they were too narrow and the shoes were not made of leather
Best affordable shoes on the market thanks amazon
Love the shoes always been a fan of reebok
these shoes are wonderful.they exceeded my expectations.great price and good fit. wish I had bought another pair.
Just the right size; thanks

Usually I wear size 9 almost in all sneakers  brands. However, these sneakers were small and narrow. I tried to usem but my fingers coudn't resist it.. It seems to be a good pair of sneakers. But I couln't use it more. So I returned them.  :(
its too small, returned it

I live in these shoes. They are perfect for everyday walking and comfort. They fit as I expected and I took my normal size. Definitely need to order more in different colors. I like these more than my expensive Nikes and they look better as well.

These sneakers were well-made. The whiteness of the shoe is really bright, giving a nice emphasis on the logo and a distinct contrast between the white laces, logo, and the predominantly black upper. The insoles are soft and comfortable. The heel area is lined with a soft, textured material, thus providing the heels with stability and comfort. Overall, this shoe was stylishly built for comfort, perfect for daily wear. The only downside I can think of is perhaps the ease in which the shoes can get stained, especially since the outsole is mainly white in colour. But I guess that is what you get for buying shoes of this colour.
Very nice, comfortable and good make. They look strong and very classic, I love this kind of sport shoe style
It was as expected. Now  looking for new Clark's for kids

I have been wearing these shoes around the house for about 15 years now.  They are sturdy, cool, and do not track a bunch of dirt and rocks into the house.  They are also consistent so I can just order them on line with confidence of what will show up.
Really sharp looking sneakers
No game or gimmicks.  The shoes look great.  No tears, missing stitches or any red flags.  They fit quite nice.  Just as I expected.
I think order too big of size so they are alittle big?
Comfortable all around shoes for my boring lifestyle of short walks and light gardening.  Have been buying them for years and wear them everyday.
Great shoes. But definitely need to go down a size.
Very nice and comfortable shoes, but I always buy them 1 size larger, because they tend to run small.
Do not waste ~$40 on these shoes.  They are very poor quality and you'd be better off buying something in the store.  Plus they are not light grey, but tan.  Sending these back.
My grandson was very satisfied with the fit and looks of this sneaker.  He was very pleased to find a sneaker is this very difficult size.
I have a pair for a long time that are getting a bit worn. Found these and thought why not. great price too,.
I bought these for my significant other and he really likes them. He had never owned a par of Reebok's before and says that they are really comfortable and fit him like a tee.. Martha
This was a good price on a hard to find style. I have purchased a number of these style shoe in the past so that I know them well.
Looks awesome, pretty much my style :)
Love this Reebok product!
I've had these shoes for 10 months and wear them 4 hours a day 5 days a week and the tread has already worn flat.
Reebok, awesome as always. 200% recommended. Great seller, delivered on time.  canÃ‚Â´t expect any better
Firme shoes been wearing them for some time now love how they feel on my feet I highly recommend them.
Bought these for my Dad, he loves these!
Love me some martens. Always a perfect fit, took almost no time to break in. Could stand some insoles, but no issues otherwise. I get mad compliments on these. never go out of style it seems.
Cradles your foot.  Very comfortable.  Columbia always has the best footbed.
The shoe arrived as stated and was a perfect fit. They are very comfortable and I am very pleased. Could not find them at local Beall's store.
wish i could find them in black, but I love this
They fit like regular docs and look great.  Hardly tell they are Doc Martens except the sole gives it away.  Great design.
Got it at a great great price. Shoes fit well as expected. Very happy with the purchase.
As described; must wear thin socks as these fit exactly as requested. Look cool on the screen but actually look kinda dorky, but then again I do have big feet! Perfect for work.
These fit perfectly.  They were great for work.  I stand on my feet all day long, day after day.

Bought for my wife, she say's:"possibly the best pair of shoes I have ever owned.  The suede interior is pillow soft, it's like slipping on a pair of kid gloves. I wear them without socks, they are perfect.  I needed a larger toe box as I have messed up my toes from years of tight "fashionable" shoes. These are so comfortable and cute.  Not an ugly orthopedic shoe, they look like a pair of little girls Mary Janes. I'm so glad I bought them. I spent a week researching all the flats on Amazon before I picked these."
And so I was motivated to buy this style for my costume. But I will wear them many other days. They are very cute and comfy. It's a dressy tennis shoe. LOL I love this shoe!
Size was good, but the strap across the top needed to be longer.  I have a very high arch and have problems finding shoes that will not be to tight across the top of foot.  I had to send these back.

For wide, knobby feet, the best.  Far nicer and better built than Drews.  I've always worked and walked hard and long. These kept me going.  Finally tossed my second pair.  Have 2 pair for daily use and one for dress.  Just ordered my 6th pair for backup.  PS  Great price. GET'EM before they are priced up, disappear or the quality declines.  Best good looking, (hubby thinks they are cute!), and comfy shoes I've ever had.

Best fitting and most confortable shoe I have ever had and I have problem feet, bunions, etc.  I have many pairs of this style but wish they would put this comfort in other styles.  So many of my friends have the Jamie Pump.  It looks like we found a sale some place.
No break-in period needed.  They fit comfortably from the very first day.  Perfect with dress pants for a day at the office and also look great with jeans.  I'll definitely be ordering others soon!!

I am a fan of this shoe.  I bought this pair to replace my worn out black pair.  I also own this style in brown and blue.  It's an excellent city and office walking shoe and looks stylish.  These shoes are very enduring.  Had the pair I replaced for avbout five years.
I have very narrow feet. These shoes fit well.
the shoe runs to large
Will be great for work or casual.  Finally got the dress up shoe for jeans.

Have worn this exact shoe for years but my feet have changed & I find it necessary to be fitted "in store" for proper fit now. However, I highly recommend this shoe. Amazon made it very easy to return. I did so. sadly.

The fit is fantastic. I wear a 10W and it is hard to get shoes that are narrow enough in the heel with a wide foot. The heel is snug so I do not walk out of them They are leather which means I can shoot them with Shoe Stretch to get a perfect fit. I have had this style before  - the shoes are 8 yrs old, and they wear like iron. I will get another pair in most likely black. The price is good - remember they are leather and will hold up for a long time. I will be wearing these for a long time. The color is good in red, not quite a bright red but they go with my clothes.. Of all the flats I have, these are the ones I walk a good while in.
Comfortable and fit perfect!

I have a very narrow foot (3A w/ 6A heel) and have to wear flats because of my age.  I have actually worn my sameTrotters Liz for over 25 yrs and have them in many colors.  They are well made and wear well.  I have had new heels put on them and new toe "soles" put on them many times over the years.  I even have a VERY thin, hard orthotic for over-pronation that I put in them.  Can't say enough about Trotters.  Have worn that brand since they were called Old Maine Trotters when I was a kid.
I have wide toes and somewhat narrow heal. I wear 7.5 D and I could not even fit my toes into the shoe. very unsatisfied. No shipping label to send them back.  Another good shoe for the yard sale.

Have had a pair like this in the past and wore them til they were no longer wearable!  Happy to have another pair.  They are a bit snug across the toes at widest part of foot, but I know from my previous pair that will stretch a bit.
WE buy this shoe all the time they are good
Very comfortable. Not breaking period needed.
Thought I was ordering a 7 1/2 but a size 7 came.. As a result, I'm not sure if I should have ordered a 7 1/2 M instead of N.

I take a size 8W shoe and I bought these shoes in that size last year. I love them but they fall off of me! The only way I can wear them is with heavy socks, which really doesn't suit the look of the shoes. So I figured I'd try the same shoes in a regular width. The width seemed okay, but the "flaps" (the curved parts) of the shoes were so tight that it made them unwearable. I was surprised because I've never had that problem. Disappointing, for sure, especially because they're really nice shoes.
I love this shoe, it fitted so comfortable and true to size
The style was a little different from what I expected but it was a please ant surprise
Fits true to size and shoes are exactly as described.

I was ambivalent when first trying on the loafer and had decided to return it but my wife intervened.  The shoe fits well and is quite comfortable in spite of some comments that it runs large.  My issue was with the looks of the loafer.  It is clunky, too dark and will not work when wearing shorts.  It is only suitable with long pants.  I have decided to keep the shoe for travel purposes as most loafers will not support the foot as well when walking long distances as this shoe should.  It would have been more attractive as a lighter colored shoe with less fancy stitching.

I only buy Clark's since I tried them out a few years ago.  Gave these a try in the same size as the rest of mine and they are uncomfortably tight.  I've worn them for 3 days hoping for a little give but they feel the same.  The problem I see is there is no give on the tongue area because there is no elastic there.  They squeeze my foot too tight making the shoe feel very narrow.  Disappointed in this style, but still like the brand overall.

I have bone spurs that come and go. Not very bad but they can at times make it so I miss a day of work because I can't walk. I've been wearing these for about a week and I even went to a baseball game and entered the opposite end of where I was seated. Needless to say I walked a lot that day. A lot !!  My feet are feeling great. I'm so glad I got these after reading reviews of people being on their feet with these shoes and how happy they were with them.. They're a great pair if shoes. Comfortable, and they look great in shirt and ties and just as good with jeans on.. Only downside is maybe they run a tad too big. But they still fit comfortably. I guess if I was younger I would "have room to grow" but I'm not so they're a little big in that sense.
very comfortable shoes .Great price
Nice shoes, fit well out of box, feel even better after break-in period.  Easy, comfortable to walk in.

Great shoes. Great for work. Great with dress pants or jeans. Light and comfortable. Paid about half the price than at the store. They're usually around $90 in the store (not the $150 as listed on Amazon.)  Pleased with the shoes.
Very nice and comfortable shoes.
Nice leather, light and comfortable.

This is my 2nd pair. It took me a couple days to break this pair in. The 1st day gave me a blister on my heel but now they seem fine. My original pair lasted for years. I bought the 9.5 just like my original pair. The fit was good and true, but maybe the heal blister was just from break in or maybe I needed a 10. They seem fine now. Clarks are super comfy. I'd buy another pair.
I love these shoes it's my new second pair
THESE are Clarks! the name speaks for themselfs! buying more pairs of shoes from clark

I own a pair of these in Brown and they are my favorite pair because they fit a little better. I looked all over in the stores to try to find these but I could not so I found them here on Amazon. What was I thinking? Should have save a lot of time and gas and just ordered them here to begin with. These are a little wider than I had hoped, but not bad.
Beautiful shoe. I've had them before. A tad large but this allowed me to swap out the inner sole. Sturdy but surprisingly light.
I will tell to all my friends!
The pictured color wasn't what arrived. The color variations on the posted photo weren't as defined as they when they arrived
This is a nice shoe but not the same quality as the original.  The sole is lighter but harder neoprene that I am sure will last but isn't as comfortable.
It's small but I gave it to my son and I would love another one size 13

It's a good shoe.  Fits well and is comfortable.. Just so happens the first time I wore it was during the rain. With. a little moisture on the sole, these shoes squeak loudly on hard wood and. vinyl floors.  I'm going to find out if I can coat the bottom with something to. stop the squeaking.
My husband likes the model, they are very comfortable with excellent quality and cheap.

I had tried these on at a store a while ago and really liked them, but didn't need brown shoes at the time and wasn't ready to make an impulse purchase at the store price. Then I saw them on sale here and jumped at the opportunity. They look great and fit fairly well--there's a bit too much vertical space inside, leaving them slightly loose for me, but some thin inserts took care of that.

A very good, stylish shoe.  It is very versatile in that it can be worn with everything from jeans to slacks with a sports coat.  The only drawback would be a lack of cushioning, but other than that it is a great shoe.
Like it for the price.

I've bought three of these pairs. The first pair were comfortable from the first moment I put them on. The second pair required a few days of adjusting to my feet, while the third pair took about two weeks of blisters before they started feeling comfortable. I'd rate them 5 stars, 4 stars, 3 stars based on the experience, so 4 stars overall.
Great product I like it.

I wear these shoes mostly with jeans. They are extremely comfortable, and slip off and on easily, so are very convenient, especially as you go through security when you travel. I have had them for quite some time, I use them often, and they still look great. a good buy!
Fits as I hoped
Second pair and love them. I use the old ones (4 years) to garden in now.
Pretty colors and a great fit!
These are cute, comfortable and cool on hot days.  They do run 1/2 size small.  I normally wear an 8 and ordered an 8 1/2 and they fit perfect.  I even wear them to walk the dog.
I use these almost everyday!!! Fantastic.

I love the fit of these shoes, I love the performance, I love the wide front, easy on and off, I love the color!. I will pursue more Keen products. My sister wears the shoes and loves them. I am sold! I am happy!

My second pair - got these cuz I loved the purple color, they were on sale (which doesn't happen often) & I knew I loved the way these sandals fit & feel. They're the best. Can walk all day/night in them. Highly recommend!
My first pair and I love them.  They are really comfortable.  I am sure I will purchase more as needed.
I love these. Very comfortable to wear all day. My feet don't get tired like they do on my other shoes. I wear them all the time.
The family has had several pairs of these for a couple of years.  Great shoe and love it in all conditions.
Re the sizing, when ordering I based it on another pair of keen shoes I have. They feel slightly smaller but the shoes overall are comfortable and light, which is why I bought them.

i bought keen venice in a bargin bin 7 years ago, and wore them at every opportunity. they finally fell apart, and i have missed them so. ordered another pair right away. tried the whisper, but it just seemed a poor sub for the venice and the foot bed is much flatter in the whisper. so far, these seem exactly the same in construction and fit. im hoping to get many more years out of my 2014 venices.

If you are looking for comfort, this is the shoe. I did read the reviews prior to ordering and there were many reviews that stated these shoes ran about a half size small. I did ordered a 9 (as I wear a woman's 8.5). Keen has always made great lasting, durable and most of all COMFORTABLE shoes. I would recommend these 100 times over!
I am very pleased. They arrived quickly and fit me well. The reduced price is very much appreciated.
They are Keene need I say more.

These were to replace the same model that I bought 5 years ago that were worn out from so much wear! I love that they are waterproof, I can hike in them and not slip, and the bumper protects my toes. I also like that when my feet get hot they don't seem to make the shoes smell funny.
I just wish I could afford to have a pair in every color.  I think I have even talked some friends into wearing them.
I love these. My third pair of keens.
my favorite sandal. cant go wrong with keen.  Comfortable, waterproof
Just needed a larger size.  New pair fit right out of the box. Super comfortable!  Love my Keens!
Good quality comfort sandals.  I wear them everywhere.

I even brought them on a month long trip to India, and wore them more often than my hiking boots and walking shoes.
They fit well and give lots of support. I work as a tour guide and survive the day with no pain. I do have arthritis in my hips and these shoes save the day!

The color (petrol/twilight) is a little darker in person than in the picture-- I thought they sent cobalt (dark blue) at first, but I think the picture just makes it look lighter than it is.

Sending back and trying again.

I also milk a goat several times a day and need foot gear that comes off my feet easily and doesn't require socks.. However, these also work for me in fall and even winter with thick socks. My two other Keen sandals are much heavier (Newport). and one is more of a shoe style--they just feel too heavy and klutzy.. also, because they are waterproof I can hose off the mud/soil frequently and they still look like new!. Years ago I bought a pair of Avia shoes with the Cantilever design and they have been the most comfortable for my feet. Since they have become "yard shoes," I have purchased other well name brands to replace these but none offered the same comfort and support.  I was happy to find these online. Since I have funny feet (bunions and a long second toe :-) ,  I was concerned about sizing and fit as some reviewers stated that these ran narrow and short. I took a chance and I am glad I stayed with my usual size of 7.5. I feel there is plenty of room in the toe box and they don't appear short at all. No second toe banging at the tip of the shoe!! YAY! The mesh design is also great as it appears durable, yet flexible, for some of the other problem areas of my feet. From the impact of the way I walk, I also have a tendency to blow out the backs of the heels of all my shoes. However, my first pair of Avias have held up well and I'm hoping these will do the same. I'm guessing it's the Cantilever design that helps with this. Regardless, I am enjoying these shoes and I think I'll skip going with any other brand of "tennis shoes" and stay with what works. On a side note, my mother-in-law has also mentioned to me that Avias are the only shoes that are comfortable for her feet so this company is doing something right! Too bad you can't find their stuff in too many stores.

These are excellent shoes, but I have found that taking out the soft insole and putting in a leather one makes them even better. The original soft insole allows my feet to move too much in the shoe and I get that burning feeling on the soles of my feet at the end of a long day. But that's just what my big feet seem to like. Yours might like the original insoles.. The construction of the shoe is very good and I like the black leather better than the other colours because it is a bit softer breaks in quicker. I am a very big, heavy man and my shoes only last about a year, but New Balance shoes seem to give good value for money in my opinion.. I've read a lot of reviews lately from people complaining about the quality of these shoes going down, but for I think people expect too much for what is basically a synthetic sole glued to a leather upper.. I used to repair shoes back in the stone age when leather soles were stitched to leather uppers and a good pair of shoes took a year to break in. Mind you, then they were good for the next 20 years!. Since then we have gotten used to the Sport / Walking / Hiking / Running / Cross training blah blah blah shoes, and we expect one pair of shoes to do every thing well and on a budget.. Well news flash people. you get what you pay for. These are a very good, everyday walking shoe and I'll be happy with a solid years work out of them. Anything more is a bonus. If you want more, then pay a craftsman to hand make a pair for you and be prepared to pay a lot of money for the privilege of owning them. Those are the shoes you can have repaired when the sole wears out, and you own them for 10 or 20 years.. And until I discovered how to use the internet thingy I have been paying $139.95 for the same shoes here in Australia! Think about that next time you read about someone complaining about $60 walking shoes.. And now. Thank goodness for Amazon. I can afford quality shoes with out having to sell one of the kids. again. (If you train them right, then they come back like homing pigeons! JUST kidding! :). I have 3 pairs of these shoes and have replaced all the insoles with leather ones and alternate them every day. They all still look like new and feel great.
